HEADWORD: Wallaba
<hw>Wal"la*ba</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
leguminous tree (<spn>Eperua falcata</spn>) of Demerara, with pinnate
leaves and clusters of red flowers. The reddish brown wood is used for
palings and shingles.</def> <au>J. Smith (Dict. Econ. Plants).</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wallaby</ent>⟦br⟧
